# Pacific Engagement visa (subclass 192)Pacific Engagement

Pacific Engagement visa (subclass 192)
Pacific Engagement

This visa allows people of Pacific island countries and Timor-Leste to live and work in Australia permanently.

This visa allows people of Pacific island countries and Timor-Leste to live and work in Australia permanently.
Published
Page Content
​

​From 1 May 2025, there are two streams of the Pacific Engagement visa (subclass 192) – the Pacific Engagement stream and the Treaty stream.

​From 1 May 2025, there are two streams of the Pacific Engagement visa (subclass 192) – the Pacific Engagement stream and the Treaty stream.

This means that ballots for 2025-26 are specific to each stream.

This means that ballots for 2025-26 are specific to each stream.

## Pacific Engagement stream

Pacific Engagement stream

Known as the ‘Pacific Engagement visa’, this stream is for eligible Pacific island and Timor-Leste nationals.

Known as the ‘Pacific Engagement visa’, this stream is for eligible Pacific island and Timor-Leste nationals.

The Pacific Engagement visa ballot for Pacific island and Timor-Leste nationals closed on 25 August 2025.​​

The Pacific Engagement visa ballot for Pacific island and Timor-Leste nationals closed on 25 August 2025.​

## Treaty stream

Treaty stream

The Pacific Engagement visa (subclass 192) – Treaty stream (Tuvalu) is for Tuvaluan nationals only and implements Australia’s obligations under the Australia-Tuvalu Falepili Union treaty.

The Pacific Engagement visa (subclass 192) – Treaty stream (Tuvalu) is for Tuvaluan nationals only and implements Australia’s obligations under the Australia-Tuvalu Falepili Union treaty.

The Treaty stream ballot for Tuvalu nationals closed on 18 July 2025.

The Treaty stream ballot for Tuvalu nationals closed on 18 July 2025.
